 point of perfection (which we're trying) you would end up with a game with "potentials" rather than "accomplishments", and that's one thing we don't want to do. <P>We find ourselves in the same situation as many rpgs before us. Somehow we managed to put it all in, now we have to polish and finish it. At this point in time we're still categorizing and cataloguing all the bugs that need to be solved, then when that's done, we need to actually solve all of them. It does not look like we'll be able to do this within 3 months, which is why CDV has prudently moved the release date to Q2. Next month we will be able to far more accurately judge how much time we still need to finish it all, but as I said, 3 months is probably not enoguh. Hence the delay.<P>Believe me, there's nobody else in the world who wants to finish this game as soon as possible than us, so we're doing everything we can.<P>Lar</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Alrik Fassbauer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Good Luck !  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/icons/icon14.gif">  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/wink.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Nemisis Dragon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thanks for making it more clear Lar.<BR>Yes, I wish the Larian Studios also good luck with fixing the bugs   <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/icons/icon14.gif"> That's a better choice than thousand of patches   <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/wink.gif"><P>But can you mayve change at least the   <IMG ALIGN=top SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/div.gif"> demo release date? 4 weeks before release...long waiting...too long   <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/wink.gif"><p>[This message has been edited by Nemisis Dragon (edited 22-12-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Myrthos</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Oh well in a way it sucks of course. Knowing that almost every RPG out there suffers from the same problem strengthens me in the belief that developers really can not estimate time and effort  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/biggrin.gif"><P>Just kidding. I'm sure that the Larians and CDV wished things were differently also and we have seen enough games coming out the last years that suffer from too many bugs and got burried because of that. So I hope you squash all those pesky little critters in the software (or at least a lot of them  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/wink.gif">)<P>------------------<BR>Webmaster of <A HREF="http://www.locusinn.com" TARGET=_blank>The Locus Inn</A><BR>Editor and Web Dude at <A HREF="http://www.rpgdot.com" TARGET=_blank>RPGDot</A><BR>Also hacking away at <A HREF="http://gothic.rpgdot.com" TARGET=_blank>Gothic@RPGDot</A><BR>And trying to keep things running at <A HREF="http://www.lidiumonline.com" TARGET=_blank>LidiumOnline</A><BR>P.S. Long signatures are for losers...</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">the alien</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Don't get paranoia over there while fixing these bugs.Good luck.</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ragon der Magier</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well, as long as severe funding problems are not the real cause behind this, i´m fine with this decision. You could even move the release a year further on for my part then( <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/badsmile.gif">!<P>I concur with Myr´s opinion and therefore wish you even more luck for hunting down those bothering little cockroaches and relatives.<BR>Because if you